            <div>
                <entry xml:id="Laa1c1830bcff435aa882ea042aa26537" n="12347">
                    <form>
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዓዬ</foreign>
                    </form>
                    <sense xml:lang="en" source="#traces" xml:id="Tmain"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote> ʿāye </quote>
                        </cit> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወበሣልስት፡ ዕለት፡ ይጥዕም፡ ፭፡ ኅጠተ፡ እምፍሬ፡ ዳዕሮ፡ ወእምአኮ፡ ፭ ፡ ፍሬ፡ ዓዬ።</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote> ‘On the third day he would eat five grains of sycamore’s fruit or else five fruits of ʿaye.’ </quote>
                        </cit> <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 30 (326) l. 7-9 (ed.); 31 (327) l. 10-11 (tr.)</citedRange>
                        </bibl> (‘I could not retrieve <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>ʿaye</quote>
                        </cit> in Gǝʿǝz, nor in Arabic. It is attested in Tǝgrǝñña (but it cannot be excluded that the source is Gǝʿǝz), meaning “diospyros mepsiliformis”, a very large tree with broad shiny leaves and edible, date-like fruit”, <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:DaBassano1918DictTgr"/>
                            <citedRange unit="col."> 703</citedRange>
                        </bibl>. It is otherwise known as Jackalberry or African Ebony or diospyros abyssinica. The corresponding Amharic entries are <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>särćin</quote>
                        </cit> {<foreign xml:lang="am">ሰርቺን</foreign>}, cf. <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Kane1990DictAmhVol1"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 490</citedRange>
                        </bibl> or <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>säläććäñ</quote>
                        </cit> {<foreign xml:lang="am">ሰለቸኝ</foreign>}, cf. <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Kebede2012Trees"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 104-105</citedRange>
                        </bibl>.’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 31 (327) n. 16</citedRange>
                        </bibl>) <nd/> </sense>
                </entry>
